### Quality Checklist

Before finalizing a release description, ensure:

- [ ] Title includes version number with emoji
- [ ] Summary is clear and concise (2-3 sentences)
- [ ] Features are user-focused and reference visible UI elements
- [ ] Installation instructions cover all platforms (macOS, Windows, Linux)
- [ ] Installer types are correctly referenced (`.dmg`, `.exe`, `.deb`, `.rpm`, `.AppImage`)
- [ ] Emojis are used consistently and appropriately
- [ ] Language is accessible to end users (not overly technical)
- [ ] Technical jargon matches project terminology (UI element names)
- [ ] All major changes since last release are included
- [ ] Formatting is clean and scannable with proper markdown

### Version Number Extraction

When generating releases, extract version from:
- Primary: `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` ‚Üí `version` field
- Secondary: `src-tauri/Cargo.toml` ‚Üí `version` field in `[package]` section

Both should be kept in sync, but `tauri.conf.json` is the source of truth for the desktop app version.
